 <h3>New St.Isaac’s Office Centre through to the final round of the project competition</h3>
<p>The New St.Isaac’s Centre is one of three finalists for the award "Best development project implemented on the Russian real estate market in 2010" in the category of Heritage (Restoration) and was invited to participate in the FIABCI PRIX D'EXCELLENCE contest , which will be held during the FIABCI World Congress in May 2011.<br /><br />
</p>
<p> <img src="/images/news-2.jpg" alt="" /> </p>
<p>The ceremony took place on September 8 at the Lenexpo press-center  during the 4th International Investment Forum on Real Estate - PROEstate. The all-Russian contest, "Best development project implemented on the Russian real estate market in 2010", is organised by the Russian National Office of the World Federation of Real Estate Professionals of Real Estate FIABCI-Russia and the Guild of Managers and Developers of Commercial and Industrial Real Estate in 8 categories, in order to identify and encourage the most successful  Russian companies working on the real estate development market to promote advanced Russian business technologies in the global professional community, and to strengthen national standards.  <br />The Chairman of the contest committee is the vice-governor of St. Petersburg, I.Metelsky. </p>
